    "body": "So, you are correct that it is valid rlp. It's a bit tricky to handle this, though. I'm not sure how to best handle it, because \"normally\" invalid txs are caught during \"apply\", when we iteratively apply them to the state. \r\n\r\nThis error happens much earlier in the pipeline. So if we have three transaction, and reject the first during rlp parsing, at `index 0`, then hand off the remaining two to \"apply\", then that part will again number them remaining ones from `index 0`. \r\n\r\nSo in order to fix it, we need to pass a list of tuples like `( nil , error), (tx, nil) ...` into the `apply`.  Or something like that. \r\n\r\nrlp:\r\n```\r\\r\n```",
